## Diagnosis

The ETRO essay renderer is faithfully converting every `**bold**` span from the source markdown into `<strong>` tags, then rendering them unstyled or with default browser bold — resulting in 36 decorative/editorial bold markers that were never meant to survive into final presentation. Simultaneously, the section bodies lack sufficient vertical rhythm or typographic hierarchy, so the reader can't orient themselves between sections.

---

## Root Cause

**AP-072 (Markdown Passthrough Without Editorial Sanitization)** — The source markdown was written as a *working draft* with scan anchors (`**Per user.**`, `**Scaffolding.**`) that are authorial scaffolding, not semantic emphasis. Passing this raw markdown straight to a renderer without a sanitization/transform layer promotes draft artifacts to publication-level UI.

**EAP-027 (Absent Inter-Section Breathing Room)** — Section bodies are stacked without sufficient spacing tokens between them, and there is no visual affordance (rule, spacing, label treatment) that signals a new section has begun.

---

## Fix

### 1. Strip editorial bold anchors at the serializer/transform layer

Create a remark/rehype plugin (or a simple string pre-processor if you're not using remark) that removes `<strong>` nodes whose text matches the scan-anchor pattern: short (≤ 4 words), ends in a period, and contains no surrounding sentence context.

**`src/lib/prose/stripEditorialBold.ts`**

```typescript
import type { Plugin } from 'unified'
import { visit } from 'unist-util-visit'
import type { Strong, Text } from 'mdast'

/**
 * Remark plugin — removes <strong> nodes that are authorial scan anchors.
 *
 * Heuristic: a bold node is editorial if:
 *   1. Its entire text content is ≤ 4 words, AND
 *   2. It ends with a period, AND
 *   3. It is the first (or only) inline in its paragraph.
 *
 * These were used as working-draft section labels and must not survive
 * into the published render. (AP-072)
 */
const EDITORIAL_BOLD_RE = /^([A-Z][^.]{0,40})\.$/ // Capitalized, short, ends in period

export const stripEditorialBold: Plugin = () => (tree) => {
  visit(tree, 'strong', (node: Strong, index, parent) => {
    const text = node.children
      .filter((c): c is Text => c.type === 'text')
      .map((c) => c.value)
      .join('')

    const wordCount = text.trim().split(/\s+/).length

    if (EDITORIAL_BOLD_RE.test(text.trim()) && wordCount <= 4) {
      // Replace strong node with its plain text children — demote, don't delete
      parent?.children.splice(index as number, 1, ...node.children)
    }
  })
}
```

**Wire it into your MDX/remark pipeline:**

**`src/lib/prose/markdownConfig.ts`**

```typescript
import { stripEditorialBold } from './stripEditorialBold'

export const remarkPlugins = [
  stripEditorialBold,
  // ...other plugins
]
```

If you're using `next-mdx-remote` or `@next/mdx`:

```typescript
// next.config.ts  (or wherever you configure MDX)
import { remarkPlugins } from './src/lib/prose/markdownConfig'

const mdxConfig = {
  options: {
    remarkPlugins,
  },
}
```

---

### 2. Harden legitimate `<strong>` so the few real ones are purposeful

Any bold that *does* survive the filter should render with a deliberate style — not browser-default. This prevents the "soup of bold" even if an edge case slips through.

**`src/styles/prose.css`** (Tailwind 4 `@layer components`)

```css
@layer components {
  .prose-elan strong {
    /* Purposeful emphasis: weight + color shift, never decoration */
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold); /* 600, not 700 */
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
}
```

---

### 3. Restore inter-section hierarchy

The core problem is that section bodies are siblings with no structural gap or divider. Apply a consistent section rhythm component.

**`src/components/essay/EssaySection.tsx`**

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'

interface EssaySectionProps {
  heading?: string
  children: React.ReactNode
  index: number
  className?: string
}

/**
 * Wraps each essay body block.
 *
 * Hierarchy system (EAP-027 fix):
 *   - mt-16 between sections (large breathing room)
 *   - Optional ruled separator on sections 2+ (visual hard stop)
 *   - Section heading uses a subdued label style, not a competing heading scale
 */
export function EssaySection({
  heading,
  children,
  index,
  className,
}: EssaySectionProps) {
  const isFirst = index === 0

  return (
    <section
      className={cn(
        'relative',
        !isFirst && 'mt-16 pt-16 border-t border-border-subtle',
        className,
      )}
    >
      {heading && (
        <h2 className="
          mb-6
          font-sans text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest
          text-text-tertiary
          select-none
        ">
          {heading}
        </h2>
      )}

      {/* prose-elan scopes all markdown output */}
      <div className="prose-elan">
        {children}
      </div>
    </section>
  )
}
```

**Usage in your essay page:**

**`src/app/(frontend)/work/etro/page.tsx`** (or wherever sections are mapped)

```tsx
import { EssaySection } from '@/components/essay/EssaySection'

// sections comes from Payload CMS query
{sections.map((section, i) => (
  <EssaySection
    key={section.id}
    heading={section.heading}
    index={i}
  >
    <MDXRemote source={section.body} options={{ mdxOptions: { remarkPlugins } }} />
  </EssaySection>
))}
```

---

### 4. Tighten prose spacing tokens

**`src/styles/prose.css`** (additions)

```css
@layer components {
  .prose-elan {
    /* Paragraph rhythm */
    p + p {
      margin-top: var(--spacing-5); /* 20px — tight enough to read as one body */
    }

    /* Lists get a touch more room */
    ul, ol {
      margin-top: var(--spacing-4);
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-4);
    }

    /* Kill any residual <br> double-spacing from markdown source */
    br {
      display: none;
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Summary of Changes

| File | What changed |
|---|---|
| `src/lib/prose/stripEditorialBold.ts` | New remark plugin removes scan-anchor bold (AP-072) |
| `src/lib/prose/markdownConfig.ts` | Registers the plugin in the remark pipeline |
| `src/components/essay/EssaySection.tsx` | New section wrapper with ruled top border + label heading (EAP-027) |
| `src/styles/prose.css` | `strong` style intentionalized; paragraph + list rhythm tightened |
| `src/app/(frontend)/work/etro/page.tsx` | Uses `EssaySection` with `index` prop to drive first/rest logic |

---

## Principle

**Editorial source material and publication presentation are different artifact layers.** Markdown written in a working draft carries author scaffolding (scan anchors, structural notes, progress markers) that must be stripped at the serialization boundary — never trusted as semantic markup. Simultaneously, section hierarchy is a *spatial* problem: readers need a hard visual stop between sections (ruled border + generous margin), not just a font-size difference. Both failures stem from treating the CMS body field as a transparent passthrough rather than as raw material requiring editorial transformation.
